The paper deals with neural architectures used in Machine Translation and Image Captioning, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL), Computer Vision (cs.CV), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also proposes a verification approach to formally verify whether a network always produces outputs within a certain length, which is related to the sub-category of Software Engineering (cs.SE). However, the main focus of the paper is on evaluating model robustness and finding output-lengthening inputs, which falls under the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI, and cs.SE.
